    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>&amp; 
and Related Character Entities</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML) re-uses some of the character entities defined in XML for certain characters including the ampersand.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Characters and Entities used in XAML</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Following is the list of specific characters and the character entities that are needed to produce them, with notes on which syntax (attribute or as content of an element) might require the character entity usage. For syntax definitions, see <Hyperlink NavigateUri="67cce290-ca26-4c41-a797-b68aabc45479.xaml">XAML Syntax Terminology</Hyperlink>
.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold"/>
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Character 
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Entity 
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Notes 
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>ampersand (&amp;)
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>&amp; 

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Must be used both for attribute values and for content of an element.
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>greater-than (>)
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>&gt;
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Must be used for attribute value, but > is acceptable as the content of an element so long as 
&lt; 
does not precede it.
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>lesser-than (
&lt;)
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>
&lt;
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Must be used for attribute value, but 
&lt; 
is acceptable as the content of an element so long as > does not come after it.
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>quotation mark (")
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>&quot;
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Must be used for attribute value, but " is acceptable as the content of an element.
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>apostrophe (')
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>&apos;
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph>Must be used for attribute value, but ' is acceptable as the content of an element.
            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Remarks</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>A curly brace ({ or } character) is escaped by a different mechanism. See <Hyperlink NavigateUri="3ce3e2ad-a868-43f9-9c98-b29561cb146e.xaml">{} Escape Sequence / Markup Extension</Hyperlink>
.
    </Paragraph>

